Thanks Steve, I calculate the audio sample rate to be between 20-100ms tuning manually. Auto tuning would produce the same results and is less fatiguing on the operator. Any method that can produce clean audio samples at this rate should work, I have tried a few different ways, the radio tuning being the best so far. As with any method &#39;intention&#39; seems to be a factor in getting any results. The linear tuning of a radio is a true random method. The content of each broadcast channel is always changing, so the audio samples are always different sweeping back and forth across the spectrum. Heres a couple more from the 7/8/07 session.

&quot;This level, costing us netlink&quot; (I have heard this term &#39;netlink&#39; a few times before)

&quot;You can have children with the lightning....I knew that&quot;

Dave

Re: Question for all &quot;Frank&#39;s ghostbox&quot; owners 


That&#39;s pretty impressive, this is all manually tuned? Do you have
any other files. Granted a box is easier to just turn on and go,
but it&#39;s amazing that you can get similar results manually.

Good job
-Steve H.



